              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} was first diagnosed with hyperlipidaemia six months ago following routine workplace screening that revealed elevated total cholesterol and LDL levels [SNOMED:E78.5]. She has a background history of mild arterial hypertension, managed with ramipril, diagnosed approximately four years ago. She has no prior hospitalisation for cardiovascular events and no history of ischemic stroke [SNOMED:E78.5], though she is considered at elevated cardiovascular risk given her dyslipidaemia, hypertension, postmenopausal status, and family history of premature cardiovascular disease. She has no history of diabetes mellitus. {patientName} does not take any herbal or over-the-counter supplements regularly. She denies tobacco use and excessive alcohol consumption. BMI is 27.4 kg/m², placing her in the overweight category. She is adherent to prescribed medications and attended all recommended follow-up appointments since diagnosis."
          }
        ]
      }
    }
